        <h2 class="">Where do coffee beans come from?</h2>
        <div class="column-list">
            <div style="width:50%" class="column">
                <p class="">Coffee beans are actually the seeds of a
                    fruit that grows on trees in tropical climates. These trees are typically found in countries
                    near the equator, including Brazil, Colombia, Ethiopia, and Vietnam. The fruit, known as a coffee
                    cherry, contains two seeds or beans, which are the part that is roasted and ground to make coffee.</p>
                <p class="">
                    There are two main types of coffee beans: Arabica and Robusta. Arabica beans are generally
                    considered to be of higher quality and have a more complex flavor profile, while Robusta
                    beans are typically less expensive and have a stronger, more bitter taste. Some other less
                    common varieties of coffee beans include Liberica and Excelsa, which are grown in smaller
                    quantities and are not as widely used.</p>
